#note Josh: I told Jesse to "play the bing," and apparently from that information he realized that the only playable bing from his available pool was B8 (I)ODINATE. From this he realized that the I must've been in the bag, so instead of playing 1J ATONED, guaranteeing him an out in every case, he can play this knowing that he can go out after drawing the I. Yeah great job my dude, let's all appreciate my big mouth and Jesse's deductive reasoning for adding 15ish more points to his 163 point lead I'm sure he needed it.   JD: What's hilarious is that this is the right play for the wrong reason. I was worried about drawing a consonant to DN after AWETO, but in that case, he always has 3 Is on his rack, and can't even go out in two anyway!! AWETO is in fact 3.6 points better than ATONED even without the I inference.
